    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-25T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-10-25T08:00:00-05:00" n="702"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d702">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BB Palestine/10–2548: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">United States Delegation</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-10-25T14:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 25, 1948—2 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 477. For Lovett from Rusk. We believe
                    discussion with Shertok along lines <gloss target="#t_GADel1">Gadel</gloss>
                        291<note n="1" xml:id="d702fn1">Dated October 23, not printed; but see the
                        first footnote 1, <ref target="#pg_1502">p. 1502</ref>.</note> would be most
                    useful in light of conversations already held here between <gloss
                        target="#t_USGADel1">USGADel</gloss> and Shertok on one hand and Eban and
                    Bunche on the other (<gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 467, October 23).
                    We therefore expect to see Shertok Tuesday afternoon or Wednesday. Also coming
                    is longer telegram reference <gloss target="#t_GADel1">Gadel</gloss> 289,
                    October 23, approved by Secretary, You may wish to ask Tel Aviv to hold up
                    action if they <pb facs="1008" n="1516" xml:id="pg_1516"/> have not already
                    discussed <gloss target="#t_GADel1">Gadel</gloss> 289, October 23 with Israeli
                        authorities.<note n="2" xml:id="d702fn2">The Department at 6 p. m., October
                        25, directed Tel Aviv not to discuss <gloss target="#t_GADel1">Gadel</gloss>
                        289 with the Israeli authorities, pending further instructions (telegram
                        176, 501.BB Palestine/10–2548). The following day it similarly instructed
                        Amman to refrain from discussion with Transjordan officials (telegram 29,
                        501.BB Palestine/10–2648).</note> [Rusk.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
